As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 352 people, 165 households, and 104 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|309.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 193 housing units at an average density of {{convert|169.6|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 89.77% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 9.66% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.28% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.28% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]]. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 2.84% of the population.

There were 165 households, out of which 21.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 49.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 10.9% had a female householder with no husband present, and 36.4% were non-families. 34.5% of all households were made up of individuals, and 21.8% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.13 and the average family size was 2.72.

In the town, the population was spread out, with 17.3% under the age of 18, 7.1% from 18 to 24, 22.2% from 25 to 44, 29.8% from 45 to 64, and 23.6% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 47 years. For every 100 females, there were 83.3 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 84.2 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $32,083, and the median income for a family was $40,972. Males had a median income of $37,250 versus $26,406 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $18,879. About 5.3% of families and 7.2% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 15.5% of those under age 18 and 10.7% of those age 65 or over.

